#### Parties with no elected representation

This category includes notable registered parties in Scotland that currently lack elected officials in either the Scottish Parliament or the UK Parliament. Some are Scotland-specific, while others may have broader UK-wide operations.

*   **[Abolish the Scottish Parliament Party](/Abolish_the_Scottish_Parliament_Party):** Founded in 2020, this party advocates for the [Scottish Parliament abolition](/Scottish_Parliament) and is [anti-devolution](/Devolution_in_the_United_Kingdom), promoting [Scottish unionism](/Unionism_in_Scotland). Its leader is John Mortimer.
*   **[Animal Welfare Party](/Animal_Welfare_Party):** Established in 2006, this party focuses on [animal welfare](/Animal_welfare). The leader is Vanessa Hudson.
*   **[British National Party](/British_National_Party):** Founded in 1982, it is associated with [British fascism](/British_fascism), [White nationalism](/White_nationalism), [right-wing populism](/Right-wing_populism), [ethnic nationalism](/Ethnic_nationalism), [ultranationalism](/Ultranationalism), and [hard Euroscepticism](/Euroscepticism). The leader is [Adam Walker](/Adam_Walker_(British_politician)).
*   **[Christian Party](/Christian_Party_(UK)):** Founded in 2004, it aligns with the [Christian right](/Christian_right), [social conservatism](/Social_conservatism), [British unionism](/Unionism_in_the_United_Kingdom), and [Euroscepticism](/Euroscepticism). The leader is Donald Boyd.
*   **[Christian Peoples Alliance](/Christian_Peoples_Alliance):** Established in 1999, it is a [Christian democracy](/Christian_democracy) party with [social conservative](/Social_conservatism) and [Eurosceptic](/Euroscepticism) tendencies. The leader is Sidney Cordle.
*   **[Communist Party of Britain](/Communist_Party_of_Britain):** Founded in 1988, it adheres to [Communism](/Communism) and [Marxism–Leninism](/Marxism%E2%80%93Leninism). The leader is [Robert Griffiths](/Robert_Griffiths_(politician)).
*   **[Independence for Scotland Party](/Independence_for_Scotland_Party):** Founded in 2020, this party's primary focus is [Scottish independence](/Scottish_independence). The leader is Colette Walker.
*   **[Independent Green Voice](/Independent_Green_Voice):** Established in 2003, this party promotes [Scottish unionism](/Unionism_in_ Scotland), [British unionism](/Unionism_in_the_United_Kingdom), and [Euroscepticism](/Euroscepticism). The leader is Alistair McConnachie.
*   **[Liberal Party](/Liberal_Party_(UK,_1989)):** Founded in 1989, it advocates for [British liberalism](/Liberalism_in_the_United_Kingdom), [Georgism](/Georgism), and [Euroscepticism](/Euroscepticism). The leader is Steve Radford.
*   **[National Front](/National_Front_(UK)):** Founded in 1967, it is associated with [British fascism](/British_fascism), [neo-fascism](/Neo-fascism), [British nationalism](/British_nationalism), and [white supremacy](/White_supremacy). The leader is Tony Martin.
*   **[Official Monster Raving Loony Party](/Official_Monster_Raving_Loony_Party):** Founded in 1983, this party is known for its [political satire](/Political_satire). The leader is [Howling Laud Hope](/Howling_Laud_Hope), also known as Alan Hope.
*   **[Reclaim Party](/Reclaim_Party):** Founded in 2020, it is associated with [right-wing populism](/Right-wing_populism) and [anti-lockdown](/COVID-19_anti-lockdown_protests_in_the_United_Kingdom) sentiments. The leader is [Laurence Fox](/Laurence_Fox).
*   **[Scottish Family Party](/Scottish_Family_Party):** Founded in 2017, it aligns with the [Christian right](/Christian_right), [social conservatism](/Social_conservatism), is [anti-abortion](/Anti-abortion), and [anti-LGBT](/Anti-LGBT). The leader is Richard Lucas.
*   **[Scottish Libertarian Party](/Scottish_Libertarian_Party):** Founded in 2012, it advocates for [libertarianism](/Libertarianism), [classical liberalism](/Classical_liberalism), [minarchism](/Night-watchman_state), [Euroscepticism](/Euroscepticism), [cultural liberalism](/Cultural_liberalism), and [Scottish independence](/Scottish_independence). The leader is Tam Laird.
*   **[Scottish Socialist Party](/Scottish_Socialist_Party):** Founded in 1998, it promotes [democratic socialism](/Democratic_socialism), [Scottish independence](/Scottish_independence), and [Scottish republicanism](/Scottish_republicanism). The co-spokespersons are [Colin Fox](/Colin_Fox_(politician)) and [Róisín McLaren](/R%C3%B3is%C3%ADn_McLaren) [c].
*   **[Scottish Unionist Party](/Scottish_Unionist_Party_(1986)):** Founded in 1986, it supports [Scottish unionism](/Unionism_in_Scotland), [British unionism](/Unionism_in_the_United_Kingdom), and is [anti-devolution](/Scottish_Parliament). The leader is Jonathan Stanley.
*   **[Social Democratic Party](/Social_Democratic_Party_(UK,_1990%E2%80%93present)):** Founded in 1990, it advocates for [social democracy](/Social_democracy), [social conservatism](/Social_conservatism), [communitarianism](/Communitarianism), and [Euroscepticism](/Euroscepticism). The leader is William Clouston.
*   **[Socialist Labour Party](/Socialist_Labour_Party_(UK)):** Founded in 1996, it promotes [socialism](/Socialism), [fiscal localism](/Fiscal_localism), [republicanism](/Republicanism), and [hard Euroscepticism](/Euroscepticism). The leader is [Arthur Scargill](/Arthur_Scargill).
*   **[Trade Unionist and Socialist Coalition](/Trade_Unionist_and_Socialist_Coalition):** Founded in 2010, it is based on [socialism](/Socialism) and [trade unionism](/Trade_unions_in_the_United_Kingdom). The leader is [Dave Nellist](/Dave_Nellist).
*   **[UK Independence Party](/UK_Independence_Party):** Founded in 1993, it is known for its [Euroscepticism](/Euroscepticism), [right-wing populism](/Right-wing_populism), [national conservatism](/National_conservatism), [economic liberalism](/Economic_liberalism), and [British nationalism](/British_nationalism). The leader is Donald Mackay.
*   **[Volt UK](/Volt_UK):** Founded in 2020, it advocates for [social liberalism](/Social_liberalism), [progressivism](/Progressivism), and [pro-Europeanism](/Pro-Europeanism). The leader is Alex Haida.
*   **[Workers Party of Britain](/Workers_Party_of_Britain):** Founded in 2019, it combines [socialism](/Socialism), [social conservatism](/Social_conservatism), [Euroscepticism](/Euroscepticism), and [British unionism](/British_unionism). The leader is [George Galloway](/George_Galloway).

#### Historical and deregistered parties

This section lists parties that are no longer active or have been deregistered.

*   **Notable historical parties:** Includes groups such as the [Communist Party of Great Britain](/Communist_Party_of_Great_Britain), [Independent Labour Party](/Independent_Labour_Party), [National Party of Scotland](/National_Party_of_Scotland), [Scottish Labour Party (1888)](/Scottish_Labour_Party_(1888)), and the [Unionist Party](/Unionist_Party_(Scotland)).
*   **Notable deregistered parties:** Includes more recent parties like [All for Unity](/All_for_Unity), [RISE — Scotland's Left Alliance](/RISE_%E2%80%93_Scotland%27s_Left_Alliance), and [Solidarity](/Solidarity_(Scotland)).

